>    onboarding walkthrough.

This project participates in the Bifrost team's internal Claude Code plugin
marketplace (`bifrost-internal`). Plugins are distributed **LAN-only** via
`https://files.uuhfn.cloud/git/bifrost-internal-plugins.git` and curated by
the marketplace admin pipeline on Server B.

## Always Do

- **Use the internal marketplace** for shared skills, hooks, and MCP servers:
  `/plugin install <name>@bifrost-internal`. Never fetch plugins from
  ad-hoc GitHub URLs at runtime.
- **Refresh before installing** to catch new releases:
  `/plugin marketplace update bifrost-internal`. Requires WireGuard / LAN
  reachability to Server A (`files.uuhfn.cloud`).
- **Pin versions** when reproducibility matters:
  `/plugin install hello-world-skill@bifrost-internal --version v0.1.0`.
- **Route npm / pip through the internal mirrors** (Verdaccio at
  `npm.uuhfn.cloud`, git mirrors at `files.uuhfn.cloud/git/...`). The
  `permissions.deny` block in `.claude/settings.json` is a hard fallback;
  do not loosen it without security review.
- **Report upstream changes** to the marketplace admin via
  `panel.uuhfn.cloud` when a plugin needs a new release.

## When Authoring a New Plugin

1. Clone the marketplace bare read-only:
   `git clone https://files.uuhfn.cloud/git/bifrost-internal-plugins.git`
   (push is 403 by design -- see `spec.md` section 6.3 for the upload SOP).
2. Add `plugins/<your-plugin>/` with `.claude-plugin/plugin.json`,
   `manifest.yaml`, `SKILL.md` (or hook/MCP file), `LICENSE`, `README.md`.
3. Build a release tarball locally:
   `tar czf <plugin>-vX.Y.Z.tar.gz -C plugins/<plugin> .`
4. Upload via `panel.uuhfn.cloud/marketplace/upload` (browser, while on
   the management VPN). The admin pipeline cuts the `plugins/<name>/vX.Y.Z`
   annotated tag and the render service refreshes `marketplace.json`.
5. Verify: `/plugin marketplace update bifrost-internal` then
   `/plugin install <name>@bifrost-internal --version vX.Y.Z`.

## When Offline (no VPN / no internet)

Use the seed tarball produced by `scripts/build-marketplace-seed.sh`:

```bash
tar xzf marketplace-seed.tar.gz -C /tmp/seed
export CLAUDE_CODE_PLUGIN_SEED_DIR=/tmp/seed/bifrost-internal-plugins
claude
# /plugin browse -> bifrost-internal -> hello-world-skill should appear
```

See `prompts/0519-1/marketplace-bootstrap/seed/README.md` for the full
offline workflow and SHA-256 verification.

## Never Do

- NEVER add `extraKnownMarketplaces` entries that point at public GitHub
  repos. All marketplace traffic MUST flow through `files.uuhfn.cloud`.
- NEVER paste `X-Admin-Key` / Anthropic API keys / Verdaccio bootstrap
  passwords into `settings.json`. Use environment variables sourced from
  a credential manager.
- NEVER remove items from `permissions.deny` without a documented
  exception approved in the team security review.
- NEVER bypass the upload pipeline (e.g. trying to `git push` to the bare
  repo). The Caddy mirror returns 403 on `git-receive-pack`; pushes will
  fail loudly.
- NEVER mirror upstream Claude-Code plugin sources into this marketplace
  (ADR-4 in `spec.md` section 5.2 -- LICENSE compliance).

## Tools Quick Reference

| Command | When to use |
|---|---|
| `/plugin browse` | List plugins available across all known marketplaces |
| `/plugin install <name>@bifrost-internal` | Install latest version of a team plugin |
| `/plugin install <name>@bifrost-internal --version vX.Y.Z` | Pin a specific version |
| `/plugin marketplace update bifrost-internal` | Refresh the index from Server A |
| `/plugin marketplace remove bifrost-internal` | (Emergency) drop the marketplace locally |

